"{\"uid\": \"tribune.com.pk-story-2483933-drag-queen-doubles-down-on-olympics-last-supper-mockery\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"NL  Drag queen admits the opening ceremony performance was a parody of the Last Supper despite organizers' soft apology.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 2, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newfoundland_and_Labrador\", \"score\": 0.627930972557912, \"rank\": 0.5925291257680482, \"text\": \"NL\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newfoundland_and_Labrador\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newfoundland_and_Labrador\"}, {\"begin\": 4, \"end\": 14, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_queen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Drag queen\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_queen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_queen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barbara Butch, one of the artists involved in the controversial opening ceremony of the Paris Olympics, confirmed that the performance was intended to parody Leonardo da Vinci's Last Supper.\", \"from\": 122, \"to\": 312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}, {\"begin\": 280, \"end\": 297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2693047557730497e-19, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch, who portrayed Jesus in the parody while wearing a silver headdress and low-cut dress, shared on her Instagram profile that she is a \\\"Love activist, DJ, and producer based in Paris,\\\" aiming to unite people through music.\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 540, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 335, \"end\": 340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999046931453, \"rank\": 9.529051707573304e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 421, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0333829833812479e-22, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}, {\"begin\": 495, \"end\": 500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999994417750452, \"rank\": 5.582253206216461e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She posted an image of the drag parody juxtaposed with Da Vinci's original painting with the caption:  \\\"Oh yes!\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 597, \"end\": 605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1319593697169772e-24, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Oh yes!\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 661, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new gay testament!\\\"\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The post was later deleted.\", \"from\": 687, \"to\": 714, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hard to believe the \\\"apology\\\" when the lady in the center of it made a huuuuge post about it being\\\"The New Gay Testament\\\"pic.twitter.com/ReTonFu6Lh  These confirmations contrast with the explanation offered by the Paris Olympics' organising committee, which stated that the controversial scene was an \\\"interpretation of the Greek God Dionysus\\\" aimed at highlighting the absurdity of human violence.\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 1114, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1040, \"end\": 1045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.9939477331579486, \"rank\": 0.005714618813138336, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1050, \"end\": 1058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.478436200481942e-16, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NEW: The artistic director responsible for the Paris opening ceremony says he mocked 2.4 billion Christians with drag queens so \\\"everybody feels represented.\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1163, \"end\": 1168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999994417750452, \"rank\": 5.582253206216461e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1213, \"end\": 1223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.737647559735531, \"rank\": 0.1794945587712598, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"During an interview, Thomas Jolly opened up about the \\\"beautiful responsibility\\\" he has as an \\\"artist.\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1295, \"end\": 1301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.5716688752387613, \"rank\": 0.40908699418698297, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"\\\"How do you\\u2026pic.twitter.com/qOb5CD2tQs  The French Bishops Conference criticised the performance, stating it included scenes of \\\"mockery and derision of Christianity,\\\" which they deeply regretted.\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999833471083178, \"rank\": 1.5293822048064654e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1530, \"end\": 1542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.6201874056733182, \"rank\": 0.6124157495541945, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They acknowledged the ceremony's overall beauty and joy but noted the hurt caused to Christians worldwide by these provocative scenes.\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1659, \"end\": 1669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.737647559735531, \"rank\": 0.1794945587712598, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to the backlash, Paris 2024 spokesperson Anne Descamps issued a soft apology, stating, \\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group.\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1739, \"end\": 1749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4456893519685896e-12, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1768, \"end\": 1776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the contrary, I think (with) Thomas Jolly, we really did try to celebrate community tolerance.\\\"\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, the ceremony's artistic director, echoed this sentiment, expressing that the performance aimed to send a message of love and inclusion, not to provoke or shock.\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1989, \"end\": 1995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.5716688752387613, \"rank\": 0.40908699418698297, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the apologies, the performance has sparked significant debate, with some commentators suggesting it referenced the feast of Dionysus rather than the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 2165, \"to\": 2334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2297, \"end\": 2305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.478436200481942e-16, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nonetheless, the artists' statements confirm their intention to parody the iconic painting, stirring considerable controversy in its wake.\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2473, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"COMMENTS  Comments are moderated and generally will be posted if they are on-topic and not abusive.\", \"from\": 2477, \"to\": 2576, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more information, please see ourComments FAQ  This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten,                     redistributed or derived from.\", \"from\": 2578, \"to\": 2736, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unless otherwise stated, all content is                     copyrighted \\u00a9 2025 The Express Tribune.\", \"from\": 2737, \"to\": 2836, \"entities\": []}]}"